The Senate President, Ahmad Lawan, on Saturday expressed sadness over the death of Hajia Hauwa, the mother of the Chairman, Yobe State Chapter of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Alhaji Mohammed Gadaka. Lawan in a statement by his media aide, Ola Awoniyi, in Abuja, commiserated with the Government and people of Yobe State on the passage of the centenarian, describing it as a great loss to the entire people of Yobe State. “I commiserate with the Chairman of our party in Yobe State, Alhaji Mohammed Gadaka, over the death of his mother.   Godwin Kienka: Why Nigerian sports is ‘going round in…     Onyekuru: I could stay in Galatasaray forever     Adesola Adeyemi: My experience on international runway has…   “The centenarian lived an impactful life, a life of care for her children and community. She will be sorely missed,” Lawan says. The Senate President also commiserated with friends and political associates of Alhaji Gadaka and prayed Allah to comfort all loved ones of the departed and accept her soul into Aljannah Firdaus.